"author_information": "John Steinbeck was an American author who won the Nobel Prize in Literature in 1962. He is best known for his realistic and empathetic portrayals of rural and working-class life during the Great Depression.",
"interesting_fact": "Steinbeck based 'Of Mice and Men' on his own experiences working as a migrant worker in California during the 1920s. The title is taken from a line in Robert Burns' poem 'To a Mouse,' which reflects on the unpredictability of life and the futility of planning."
